#originalTopic=Debate:_DC_handgun_ban
Previous Supreme Court decisions ruled that the Second Amendment does not apply to personal guns Cases such as U.S v Miller that were brought to the Supreme Court have contributed to making significant differences of the context in which the Second Amendment can be applied. In Us vs Miller the court established that the Second Amendment "did not guarantee a citizen's right to posses a sawed-off shotgun"
